The White House Office of Intergovernmental Affairs recently hosted a meeting with county association presidents and executive directors, in collaboration with the National Association of Counties (NACO). The purpose of the meeting was to discuss the local impact of President Biden's Investing in America agenda on communities throughout the country. Senior administration officials and county executives explored opportunities to work together on implementing various programs from the agenda, such as the American Rescue Plan, Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, CHIPS and Science Act, and Inflation Reduction Act. The meeting also addressed important issues for local governments, including broadband infrastructure, housing, and mental health care. Notable administration officials in attendance included Secretary of Transportation Pete Buttigieg, Deputy Secretary of Commerce Don Graves, Senior Advisor Tom Perez, Senior Advisor John Podesta, and Deputy Homeland Security Advisor Caitlin Durkovich.